<br>
Defensive is a very very good discipine available to guild warriors when fighting high end class monsters. If used properly if can be &quot;part&quot; of what allows guilds to actually fight monsters that quad hits for 400 to 500 plus.<br>
<br>
The discipine &quot;Defensive&quot; itself is actually a common discipine shared by rogues and monks I believe, they have similar discs with different names; yet on a warrior with a large amount of AC and Hp it's a shining ability. When the disc is popped, the warrior's damage &quot;migation&quot; factors for 3 mins jump up enormously. I've heard of warriors who would normally take 1k of damage against an uber only have their damage intake reduced to 500 or 700 points. Clerics now can wait longer to heal, as the warrior is now taking damage at a slower rate. That's a good thing, because there's of a less damage/aggro transfer to the cleric and the warrior has more of a chance to keep aggro. Ask any cleric what happens if they have to slam heals after heals immediately.<br>
<br>
There's a catch though, the warrior's own damage output is respectively reduced as well, so it becomes easier to pull the monster's focus off the warrior even further. That's not a good thing for rogues, monks, rangers, enchanters, and pretty much anyone else on the raid. A warrior on his end can off set this by a number of means: ( In the order of greatest to lest. )<br>
<br>
a. Aquire weapons that proc: aggression effects. Yes there are weapons that are out there that procs effect that do nothing more then throw a melee leaps and bounds ahead on a monster's to-kill list. Two notable weapons that do this are the Blade of Carnage and Hategiver. Unfortunately both weapons drop only from extremly high end monsters, and I mean high end. The former weapon drops of the Avatar of War, while the later drops off the Creator in the Ssar temple. Ouch.<br>
<br>
b. Aquire weapons that proc: slow type effects. Slowing a monster is an enormous jump in gaining a monter's attention. Ask any Shaman or Enchanter. Weapons that are prized with this slowing effect are: Willsapper, Wavecrasher, The Truncheon of Doom.<br>
<br>
c. Aquire fast and best ratio-ed weapons. If your going to hit for a reduced amount, why not make your hits numerous. Also aquire as much haste as possible.<br>
<br>
d. Aquire weapons that procs: a debuffing effect.<br>
<br>
e. Aquire weapons that procs: a damage over time effect, with the damage ranging around 500 point mark.<br>
<br>
f. Aquire weapons that procs: an extremely large direct damage effect. Look for damage in the range of 500 plus per process.<br>
<br>
On the group's end, everyone must keep themselves checked and do their best to do as much damage while not wasting the defensive disc by pulling aggro away from the warrior in defensive mode. That's the way VI envisioned it apparently, and that's what VI considers a good team effort. <p>Senaan Truesilver<br>Seneschal of the Knights<br>Loving husband of Joslin<br><a target=new href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=97689>Lowbie_Gear</a><br></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub66.ezboard.com/usenaantruesilver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Senaan Truesilver</A> at: 4/26/02 12:02:32 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=555555><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub66.ezboard.com/ucharcoth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Charcoth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guild Leader<br>Who let the ranger in?</span><br>  Posts: 939<br> <font color=#FFFCCC>(4/26/02 1:04:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub66.ezboard.com/fknightsoffreedom94013frm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=311.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Myrmidon and Defensive</span><hr size=1> Congratulations Senaan! It's obvious you've been anticipating this moment greatly. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
